    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains two-dimensional demographic data with 21 ordinal age categories and two quantitative percentage variables (male/female distributions). Original source data from populationpyramid.net shows characteristic population pyramid shape with declining birth rates (narrowing base) and aging population (bulge at 50-64). The mirrored bar chart maximizes data-ink ratio by eliminating redundant axes while maintaining perceptual symmetry. Cairo's principles of salience are applied through complementary color gradients (blue for males, red for females) that create immediate gender distinction. Axis mirroring follows Tufte's principle of small multiples for direct comparison. Data integrity is maintained through percentage formatting (\u2211male + female \u2264 100% per age group) with value ranges (0-4.4%) reflecting realistic demographic proportions."
